<p>Observation of broken time-reversal symmetry in the heavy-fermion
superconductor UPt3 <code class="highlighter-rouge">14-Schemm</code> <code class="highlighter-rouge">Science 345, 190 (2014)</code></p>

<blockquote>

  <p>In the normal state, strong hybridization between itinerant platinum 5d electrons and localized uranium 5f moments results in an effective mass that is ~50 times that of free electrons.</p>
